In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims November 2009 as National Alzheimer's Disease Awareness Month. He acknowledges the challenges faced by American families dealing with Alzheimer's disease and emphasizes the importance of providing support to both those suffering from the disease and their caregivers. The President also highlights the significance of ongoing research in improving treatments and potentially finding a cure for Alzheimer's. He mentions that early treatments can slow the progression of the disease, and he expresses support for embryonic stem cell research as a potential avenue for better understanding and curing devastating diseases. The article concludes with a call to observe National Alzheimer's Disease Awareness Month with appropriate programs and activities.